srabon &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; din ( bengali : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; - english : a rainy day of the month srabon ) is a bangladeshi drama film based on the novel of humayun ahmed . this movie based on a triangle tragic love story set in a classical village of bangladesh directed by the writer himself . this film was second film directed by humayun ahmed released in 1999 and won national film award . british film institute enlisted this film in the top 10 bangladeshi film ( critics ) as a 2002 cultural project on south asian cinema in 2002 .